04:46.479 --> 04:48.882
♪♪♪♪

04:48.882 --> 04:50.784
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

04:50.784 --> 04:52.485
DAVID?

04:52.485 --> 04:54.655
ANY LUCK?

04:54.655 --> 04:55.789
WELL, SOME.

04:55.789 --> 04:57.223
WITH?

04:57.223 --> 04:58.925
WELL, I COULDN'T
FIND THE ADDRESS,

04:58.925 --> 05:02.002
BUT I WAS ABLE TO
FIND THIS.

05:02.002 --> 05:03.970
WHAT'S THIS?

05:03.970 --> 05:07.440
BRUCE AND BARBARA,
THEY'RE PRIVATE EYES.

05:07.440 --> 05:10.911
MAGGIE DAY HIRED THEM
TO WATCH YOUR WIFE.

05:10.911 --> 05:13.279
HE SNAPPED THOSE PHOTOS.

05:13.279 --> 05:14.915
NOW THE YOUNG MAN IN THE PHOTO,
HIS NAME IS BENJ‐‐

05:14.915 --> 05:16.650
BENJAMIN YOUNG.

05:16.650 --> 05:19.185
OH, YOU KNOW HIM?

05:19.185 --> 05:21.054
YEAH.

05:24.190 --> 05:26.660
YES, I DO.

05:26.660 --> 05:28.629
I'M SORRY, DAVID.

05:31.164 --> 05:32.833
WHEN DID IT START?

05:32.833 --> 05:34.601
IT STARTED WHEN SHE
BAILED HIM OUT OF JAIL ‐‐

05:34.601 --> 05:35.769
AS FAR AS WE KNOW.

05:35.769 --> 05:37.871
IT WENT ON FOR QUITE SOME TIME
AT THE TOW YARD.

05:37.871 --> 05:39.806
NOW THAT'S ALL WE'VE BEEN
ABLE TO FIND OUT SO FAR.

05:39.806 --> 05:42.175
YEAH.

05:42.175 --> 05:44.711
I KNEW MAGGIE DAY
HIRED SOMEBODY.

05:44.711 --> 05:46.179
YEAH, WELL, THERE YOU GO.

05:46.179 --> 05:48.815
SO...SHE HAD MORE IMAGES?

05:48.815 --> 05:50.316
YEAH.

05:50.316 --> 05:52.686
OKAY.

05:52.686 --> 05:54.187
LOOK, DO ME A FAVOR, DAVID.

05:54.187 --> 05:56.289
DON'T LET HER KNOW
THAT BRUCE TOLD ME.

05:56.289 --> 05:59.159
HE LIKES HER TO THINK
THAT HE'S FAITHFUL TO HER.

05:59.159 --> 06:01.568
OF COURSE. I WON'T.

06:01.568 --> 06:03.036
THANK YOU.

06:03.036 --> 06:05.138
AND WE'RE STILL WORKING
THAT ADDRESS FOR YOUR WIFE.

06:05.138 --> 06:07.541
YES, VERY GOOD. OKAY.

06:07.541 --> 06:09.576
DAVID, I'M SORRY.

06:09.576 --> 06:12.478
IS THAT ALL?

06:12.478 --> 06:14.314
YEAH.

06:14.314 --> 06:17.083
OKAY.

06:17.083 --> 06:19.485
THANK YOU.

06:19.485 --> 06:22.222
LISTEN,
I'LL KEEP YOU POSTED.

06:22.222 --> 06:24.224
THANK YOU.

06:29.495 --> 06:33.600
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

06:33.600 --> 06:35.536
DAVID.

06:35.536 --> 06:36.737
KATHERYN, YOU'RE OUT.

06:36.737 --> 06:37.403
YES.

06:37.403 --> 06:38.572
IS VERONICA OUT?

06:38.572 --> 06:39.606
NO.

06:39.606 --> 06:41.608
WHO GOT YOU RELEASED?

06:41.608 --> 06:42.676
THE D. A.

06:42.676 --> 06:43.944
BUT VERONICA IS NOT OUT?

06:43.944 --> 06:47.113
ARE YOU KIDDING ME? SHE'S
NOT LETTING HER OR JIM OUT.

06:47.113 --> 06:48.782
OKAY.

06:48.782 --> 06:50.216
"OKAY"?

06:50.216 --> 06:51.417
YES, YES.

06:51.417 --> 06:52.719
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, "YES"?

06:52.719 --> 06:53.887
WE'VE GOT TO GET 'EM
OUT OF THERE, DAVID.

06:53.887 --> 06:54.921
I KNOW.

06:54.921 --> 06:56.590
WELL THEN, WHY ARE YOU
JUST STANDING THERE?

06:56.590 --> 06:58.124
I'M THINKING.

06:58.124 --> 07:00.126
[ SCOFFS ] DAVID.

07:00.126 --> 07:03.103
WE ARE DEALING WITH
A VERY DELICATE SITUATION.

07:03.103 --> 07:04.805
YES, I KNOW IT IS,
AND IT'S ‐‐

07:04.805 --> 07:06.272
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]

07:06.272 --> 07:09.743
DADGUM IT,
WHO IS CALLING ME?

07:09.743 --> 07:11.612
IT'S THE BANK.

07:11.612 --> 07:16.249
LLOYD. YOU HAVE CALLED ME
FOUR TIMES TODAY.

07:16.249 --> 07:18.685
IN CASE YOU HAVEN'T HEARD,
I'M IN THE MIDDLE OF A CRISIS,

07:18.685 --> 07:20.954
SO WHATEVER THIS IS,
IT CAN WAIT.

07:20.954 --> 07:23.089
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

07:23.089 --> 07:27.293
THANK YOU. I WILL CALL YOU
WHEN I GET A MINUTE. ALL RIGHT?

07:27.293 --> 07:28.762
GOODBYE.

07:28.762 --> 07:29.996
DAMN IT.

07:29.996 --> 07:31.965
SO WHAT ARE WE DOING
ABOUT GETTING THEM OUT?

07:31.965 --> 07:33.133
I'M WORKING ON SOMETHING.

07:33.133 --> 07:35.068
WELL,
WHY DON'T I BELIEVE YOU?

07:36.436 --> 07:38.304
I AM WORKING ON SOMETHING.

07:38.304 --> 07:40.006
I HAVE CALLED SEVERAL JUDGES
IN THIS TOWN ‐‐

07:40.006 --> 07:43.409
SEVERAL, MIND YOU, AND NONE
OF THEM ARE WILLING TO HELP.

07:43.409 --> 07:44.811
YES, I KNOW.

07:44.811 --> 07:46.412
I EVEN CALLED CARTER.

07:46.412 --> 07:47.614
MM‐HMM?

07:47.614 --> 07:50.517
AND HE TOLD ME THAT YOU'RE
NOT GETTING VERONICA OUT.

07:50.517 --> 07:51.818
THAT'S CORRECT.

07:51.818 --> 07:53.486
WHY NOT?

07:53.486 --> 07:55.255
SHE'S SAFER IN JAIL.

07:55.255 --> 07:57.758
DAVID...

07:57.758 --> 08:01.301
I KNOW THAT YOU ARE UPSET
ABOUT THIS WHOLE AFFAIR THING,

08:01.301 --> 08:03.804
AND YOU HAVE EVERY RIGHT
TO BE.

08:03.804 --> 08:06.439
BUT GET OVER IT!

08:06.439 --> 08:09.510
WE'VE ALL HAD THEM,
INCLUDING YOU, I'M SURE.

08:09.510 --> 08:12.679
SO PUT ON YOUR BIG BOY PANTS
AND TAKE CARE OF BUSINESS!

08:12.679 --> 08:15.549
YOU HAVE NO IDEA WHAT'S GOING ON
WITH VERONICA, DO YOU?

08:15.549 --> 08:17.784
YES.
I'VE SEEN THE PICTURES.

08:17.784 --> 08:19.485
THIS IS NOT ABOUT
THE PICTURES.

08:19.485 --> 08:21.722
THEN WHY DON'T YOU TELL ME
WHAT IT'S ABOUT.

08:21.722 --> 08:24.024
IT'S BEST IF YOU
DON'T KNOW.

08:24.024 --> 08:25.458
REALLY?

08:25.458 --> 08:26.560
YES.

08:26.560 --> 08:28.995
[ SCOFFS ]

08:30.363 --> 08:32.298
[ SIGHS ] DAVID...

08:32.298 --> 08:34.167
LOOK...

08:34.167 --> 08:35.669
THAT PLACE IS AWFUL.

08:35.669 --> 08:38.204
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
GET HER OUT,

08:38.204 --> 08:39.840
BRING HER HOME
SO THE TWO OF YOU

08:39.840 --> 08:42.809
CAN DISCUSS THIS AND WE CAN
ALL MOVE ON WITH OUR LIVES?

08:42.809 --> 08:45.178
DO YOU KNOW
WHERE SHE LIVES?

08:45.178 --> 08:45.979
WHAT?

08:45.979 --> 08:47.581
WHERE DOES VERONICA LIVE?

08:47.581 --> 08:48.314
I DON'T KNOW.

08:48.314 --> 08:49.049
YOU'RE SURE?

08:49.049 --> 08:50.316
YES, I'VE NEVER BEEN THERE.

08:50.316 --> 08:51.918
SHE'S NEVER EVEN GIVEN YOU
AN ADDRESS?

08:51.918 --> 08:53.654
NO! AND WHAT DOES THIS
HAVE TO DO WITH

08:53.654 --> 08:54.755
GETTING HER OUT OF JAIL?!

08:54.755 --> 08:57.023
KATHERYN, JUST LET ME
HANDLE THIS.

08:57.023 --> 08:59.826
NO ONE IN THIS TOWN
IS GOING TO HELP ME.

08:59.826 --> 09:01.301
ARE THEY?

09:01.301 --> 09:04.104
WAIT A MINUTE.
HOW DID YOU GET OUT?

09:04.104 --> 09:06.106
MAGGIE DAY.

09:06.106 --> 09:08.575
HOW DID SHE MANAGE THAT?

09:08.575 --> 09:10.677
SHE CALLED IN A FEW FAVORS.

09:10.677 --> 09:13.379
THEN WHY DIDN'T SHE CALL IN
A FEW FAVORS FOR JIM?

09:14.881 --> 09:16.950
I DIDN'T WANT TO.

09:16.950 --> 09:18.519
EXCUSE ME?

09:18.519 --> 09:21.321
LOOK, MRS. CRYER,
IT'S TOO HOT.

09:23.857 --> 09:26.059
HAS EVERYONE IN THIS TOWN
GONE MAD?

09:26.059 --> 09:28.194
THAT IS MY <i>HUSBAND.</i>

09:28.194 --> 09:29.963
WHO COVERED UP A CRIME.

09:29.963 --> 09:32.298
AND IF I WERE YOU, I'D PUT SOME
DISTANCE BETWEEN THE TWO OF YOU.

09:32.298 --> 09:33.600
IS THAT SO?

09:33.600 --> 09:37.904
YES. LOOK, I ‐‐ I'M SORRY,
MRS. CRYER, BUT HE'S GOING DOWN.

09:37.904 --> 09:40.974
HAVE YOU SEEN THE PAPER
OR ‐‐ OR THE PRESS OUTSIDE?

09:40.974 --> 09:43.644
YES. THAT'S WHY
I CAME IN THE BACK.

09:43.644 --> 09:46.580
WELL, YOU REALLY SHOULD
DISTANCE YOURSELF.

09:51.084 --> 09:53.253
OKAY.

09:53.253 --> 09:55.622
WELL...

09:55.622 --> 09:58.892
IF NO ONE WILL HELP HIM,
THEN I WILL.

09:58.892 --> 10:01.061
THAT'S NOT WISE.

10:01.061 --> 10:03.737
AND NEITHER IS ANYONE
WHO UNDERESTIMATES ME.

10:03.737 --> 10:05.672
LOOK, MRS. CRYER,
I KNOW THIS BUSINESS.

10:05.672 --> 10:07.641
AND I KNOW MY POWER!

10:07.641 --> 10:10.544
NOW YOU NEED TO GET OUT OF
THE WAY WHEN I UNLEASH IT.

10:10.544 --> 10:12.078
MOVE!

10:12.078 --> 10:13.747
[ SIGHS ]

10:13.747 --> 10:15.315
DAVID. I ‐‐

10:15.315 --> 10:17.417
MAGGIE,
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE LIED TO ME

10:17.417 --> 10:19.953
ABOUT THOSE PHOTOGRAPHS.

10:19.953 --> 10:21.655
DAVID.

10:25.491 --> 10:28.261
[ SIGHS ]

10:28.261 --> 10:31.865
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

10:48.982 --> 10:51.217
[ Ringing ]

10:51.217 --> 10:52.352
LLOYD: Yes?

10:52.352 --> 10:54.054
YES, LLOYD BOWMAN, PLEASE?

10:54.054 --> 10:55.756
THIS IS HE.

10:55.756 --> 10:58.124
THIS IS
D. A. JENNIFER SALLISON.

10:58.124 --> 11:02.202
YES, I RECEIVED YOUR FAX
AND YOUR E‐MAILS

11:02.202 --> 11:05.138
AND A COURT ORDER
THIS MORNING.

11:05.138 --> 11:07.841
SO WHY HAVE YOU BEEN IGNORING
MY CALLS THIS MORNING?

11:07.841 --> 11:11.144
I'M SORRY,
BUT I'VE BEEN VERY BUSY.

11:11.144 --> 11:12.846
LOOK, I KNOW THAT THE CRYERS

11:12.846 --> 11:15.148
DO A LOT OF BUSINESS
WITH YOUR BANK.

11:15.148 --> 11:17.250
YES, THAT'S TRUE.

11:17.250 --> 11:19.853
AND I KNOW THAT YOU
DON'T WANT TO UPSET THAT.

11:19.853 --> 11:21.955
THAT WOULD BE CORRECT ALSO.

11:21.955 --> 11:26.259
BUT YOU DO SEE THAT THE JUDGE
DID SIGN THAT ORDER?

11:26.259 --> 11:28.294
YES.

11:28.294 --> 11:29.996
SO YOU SEE EVERYTHING
IS THERE?

11:29.996 --> 11:31.598
YES.

11:31.598 --> 11:35.435
SO, WYATT WILL BE BY
THIS MORNING.

11:35.435 --> 11:37.337
MISS SALLISON,

11:37.337 --> 11:41.107
YOU DO KNOW THAT WYATT CRYER
HAS A DRUG PROBLEM?

11:41.107 --> 11:42.976
EXCUSE ME,
ARE YOU A THERAPIST?

11:42.976 --> 11:43.644
No.

11:43.644 --> 11:44.344
A DOCTOR?

11:44.344 --> 11:45.411
NO, I'M NOT.

11:45.411 --> 11:47.380
Are you some sort of a...?

11:47.380 --> 11:50.383
I AM [SIGHS]
A FAMILY FRIEND,

11:50.383 --> 11:52.686
Have been for years.
Miss Sallison,

11:52.686 --> 11:56.456
HIS MOTHER AND FATHER SIT ON
THE BOARD OF OUR BANK.

11:56.456 --> 11:59.225
AND YOU THINK THAT QUALIFIES YOU
TO MAKE THAT KIND OF ASSUMPTION?

11:59.225 --> 12:02.235
AS I SAID,
I KNOW THE FAMILY.

12:02.235 --> 12:08.174
BUT YOU DO SEE IN FRONT OF YOU
A COURT ORDER FROM A JUDGE?

12:08.174 --> 12:10.376
[ SCOFFS ] YES, I DO.

12:10.376 --> 12:12.613
OKAY.

12:12.613 --> 12:14.881
SO WHEN WYATT GETS THERE
THIS MORNING,

12:14.881 --> 12:18.051
YOU WILL RELEASE THE FUNDS
TO HIM, IS THAT CLEAR?

12:18.051 --> 12:19.720
YES, THAT IS CLEAR.

12:19.720 --> 12:20.787
Perfect.

12:20.787 --> 12:22.122
OKAY.

12:22.122 --> 12:23.557
And Mr. Bowman?

12:23.557 --> 12:24.725
YES?

12:24.725 --> 12:26.226
IF YOU CALL HIS MOTHER

12:26.226 --> 12:29.930
OR ATTEMPT TO BLOCK THIS
OR DELAY THIS IN ANY WAY,

12:29.930 --> 12:32.633
I WILL CALL THE JUDGE
AND I WILL TELL HIM

12:32.633 --> 12:34.500
THAT YOU ARE ATTEMPTING
TO TAMPER

12:34.500 --> 12:36.870
WITH THE SAFETY OF A WITNESS.
IS THAT CLEAR?

12:36.870 --> 12:38.438
YES.

12:38.438 --> 12:40.807
Thank you.

12:44.210 --> 12:45.979
[ SIGHS ]

12:57.223 --> 12:59.359
OKAY.

12:59.359 --> 13:03.837
CONFESSION TIME.

13:03.837 --> 13:05.572
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

13:05.572 --> 13:06.940
MMM.

13:06.940 --> 13:10.977
WELL, YOU'RE SHAKING.
AND YOU DON'T SHAKE.

13:10.977 --> 13:13.580
AM I?

13:13.580 --> 13:16.917
UH, YES.

13:16.917 --> 13:21.221
GIVE ME THAT.

13:25.592 --> 13:28.929
DAMN, ERICA, I HAD IT.

13:28.929 --> 13:30.597
YOU HAD WHAT?

13:30.597 --> 13:33.567
[ SCOFFS ] I HAD IT.
I HAD IT ALL.

13:33.567 --> 13:36.302
I HAD MONEY.

13:36.302 --> 13:37.938
WAS GOING TO TAKE THE BAR.

13:37.938 --> 13:40.406
PROFESSOR CANON
WROTE A RECOMMENDATION

13:40.406 --> 13:42.175
FOR ME TO TAKE THE BAR EARLY.

13:42.175 --> 13:47.213
JIM CRYER, HE TOOK IT,

13:47.213 --> 13:49.082
TOOK EVERYTHING
OUT OF MY APARTMENT.

13:49.082 --> 13:53.854
[ Voice breaking ] AND NOW,
CANON WON'T RETURN MY CALLS,

13:53.854 --> 13:56.456
SO...

13:56.456 --> 13:59.225
OH, HE'S DEAD.

13:59.225 --> 14:00.601
WHAT?

14:00.601 --> 14:01.702
MM‐HMM.

14:01.702 --> 14:03.469
YEAH, GUNNED DOWN
AT THE COLLEGE.

14:03.469 --> 14:06.339
WHAT?

14:06.339 --> 14:10.243
YEAH, APPARENTLY, IT WAS, UM,
SOME BOYFRIEND OF A STUDENT.

14:11.845 --> 14:13.079
DAMN.

14:15.649 --> 14:21.522
IT'S GOING TO TAKE ME TWO YEARS
TO TAKE THE BAR.

14:21.522 --> 14:25.692
[ SIGHS ] LOST IT.

14:25.692 --> 14:28.461
MAYBE MY MOTHER WAS RIGHT.

14:30.130 --> 14:32.132
DID YOU JUST SAY THAT?

14:32.132 --> 14:33.567
[ SCOFFS ]

14:33.567 --> 14:35.802
YEAH, SHE'S RIGHT.

14:35.802 --> 14:39.640
W‐WHAT'S GOING ON?

14:39.640 --> 14:43.510
I'M IN DEEP.

14:43.510 --> 14:46.346
WELL, YOU'VE BEEN IN DEEP
BEFORE.

14:46.346 --> 14:50.684
NO, I'VE BEEN IN DEEP
BEFORE WITH PEOPLE WHO...

14:50.684 --> 14:54.254
WHO HAD SOMETHING TO LOSE.

14:54.254 --> 14:57.958
NOW I'M IN DEEP WITH SOMEONE
WHO HAS NOTHING TO LOSE.

14:59.225 --> 15:01.267
SOMEONE LIKE WHO?

15:01.267 --> 15:04.505
WAR.

15:04.505 --> 15:06.840
CANDACE?

15:06.840 --> 15:09.510
I KNOW.

15:11.111 --> 15:13.780
PLEASE TELL ME YOU
DIDN'T CROSS HIM?

15:13.780 --> 15:16.249
I DIDN'T, REALLY.

15:16.249 --> 15:17.918
JUST DIDN'T TELL HIM
EVERYTHING.

15:19.319 --> 15:21.054
GIRL, YOU KNOW WHAT
HE DID TO TINA?

15:22.889 --> 15:25.291
I KNOW.
[ SHUDDERS ]

15:25.291 --> 15:27.393
AND JASMINE.

15:27.393 --> 15:30.697
MM‐HMM. I KNOW.

15:32.265 --> 15:36.703
WHAT DOES HE WANT?

15:36.703 --> 15:37.604
$2 MILLION.

15:37.604 --> 15:38.404
[ GASPS ]

15:38.404 --> 15:40.707
CANDACE?

15:40.707 --> 15:44.044
I KNOW.

15:45.846 --> 15:49.249
UH, PLEASE TELL ME
YOU HAVE A PLAN?

15:50.216 --> 15:55.556
THE ONLY PLAN I HAVE RIGHT NOW
IS TO FIND OSCAR.

15:55.556 --> 15:58.559
WAR WILL HURT YOU.

16:00.561 --> 16:02.669
NOT BEFORE HE HURTS
MY BROTHER.

16:02.669 --> 16:05.105
OH.

16:05.105 --> 16:06.907
YOU HAVE TO TELL BENNY.

16:06.907 --> 16:09.142
I CAN'T.

16:09.142 --> 16:11.645
I'LL, UM...

16:11.645 --> 16:13.714
I'LL GET THE MONEY
FROM ALIYAH.

16:13.714 --> 16:16.617
I'LL GET THE HUNDRED GRAND
FROM ALIYAH AND GIVE HIM THAT,

16:16.617 --> 16:20.186
AND HOPE‐‐ HOPEFULLY, IT'LL BUY
ME SOME TIME TO PAY THE REST.

16:20.186 --> 16:21.421
BUT, GIRL, THAT GIRL...

16:21.421 --> 16:23.590
IS NOT GOING TO COME UP WITH
THAT MONEY.

16:23.590 --> 16:25.526
SHE'D BETTER.

16:25.526 --> 16:27.193
CANDACE...

16:27.193 --> 16:32.198
I KNOW.

16:32.198 --> 16:33.700
LOOK...

16:33.700 --> 16:36.336
LOOK, I HAVE ‐‐ I HAVE ‐‐
I HAVE ‐‐ I HAVE ANOTHER PLAN.

16:39.272 --> 16:41.007
I CAN MORTGAGE THIS PLACE.

16:41.007 --> 16:43.109
IS IT EVEN WORTH THAT MUCH?

16:43.109 --> 16:44.210
NOT QUITE.

16:44.210 --> 16:45.546
MAYBE I CAN ASK BENNY,

16:45.546 --> 16:47.881
AND WE CAN MORTGAGE
BOTH HOUSES.

16:47.881 --> 16:50.684
WELL, HE HAS TO.

16:50.684 --> 16:54.287
I DON'T EVEN KNOW HOW
TO ASK HIM TO DO THAT.

16:54.287 --> 16:56.289
I CAN'T ASK HIM THAT.

16:56.289 --> 16:58.692
YOU HAVE TO.

16:58.692 --> 17:01.768
IF YOU TELL HIM HOW BAD
IT IS, HE WILL.

17:01.768 --> 17:06.272
IF I TELL HIM THAT THIS IS WAR,
HE WILL GO CRAZY.

17:08.008 --> 17:10.844
HE WILL GO <i>CRAZY.</i>

17:10.844 --> 17:13.680
I DON'T WANT THEM
TO GO AT EACH OTHER.

17:13.680 --> 17:16.517
WHEN BENNY GETS MAD, HE...

17:16.517 --> 17:18.685
HE DOESN'T HAVE LIMITS,
EITHER.

17:18.685 --> 17:20.854
I MEAN, WHY?

17:20.854 --> 17:22.388
WHY DO I KEEP ‐‐

17:22.388 --> 17:26.727
WHY DO I KEEP PUTTING MYSELF
IN ‐‐ IN THESE SITUATIONS?

17:26.727 --> 17:29.395
YOU KNOW?

17:29.395 --> 17:33.266
LIKE...I DON'T KNOW,
MAYBE MY MOTHER IS RIGHT.

17:33.266 --> 17:36.603
OKAY. NO, DON'T ‐‐
DON'T SAY THAT AGAIN.

17:36.603 --> 17:39.339
BECAUSE THAT WOULD MEAN
THAT MY FATHER IS RIGHT.

17:39.339 --> 17:41.642
AND BETWEEN
YOUR BIBLE‐THUMPING MOTHER

17:41.642 --> 17:44.945
AND MY PREACHER OF A FATHER...

17:44.945 --> 17:49.182
I DON'T WANT TO HEAR IT.
THEY BOTH CAN'T BE RIGHT.

17:51.317 --> 17:54.621
YOU'RE RIGHT.

17:54.621 --> 17:56.790
[ SIGHS ]

17:56.790 --> 17:59.259
OKAY.

17:59.259 --> 18:01.434
OH, E‐ENOUGH OF THIS.

18:04.104 --> 18:06.439
[ SCOFFS ] RIGHT.

18:06.439 --> 18:07.407
[ SIGHS ]

18:07.407 --> 18:09.242
LET'S GET UP
AND DO WHAT WE DO.

18:10.611 --> 18:12.779
OKAY. I'M YOUR GIRL.

18:12.779 --> 18:14.848
TELL ME WHAT WE NEED TO DO.

18:14.848 --> 18:17.918
BESIDES FINDING
OSCAR'S ASS?

18:17.918 --> 18:19.152
MM‐HMM.

18:19.152 --> 18:22.823
HE'S PROBABLY IN ANOTHER PART
OF THE WORLD RIGHT NOW.

18:22.823 --> 18:25.526
[ SIGHS ]

18:25.526 --> 18:28.729
YOU'D BETTER TELL BENNY YOU NEED
HIM TO MORTGAGE HIS HOUSE.

18:28.729 --> 18:32.465
I ‐‐ I KNOW.

18:32.465 --> 18:35.669
BUT FIRST, UM,
LET'S PAY LANDON A VISIT

18:35.669 --> 18:37.470
TO SEE IF HE KNOWS
WHERE OSCAR IS.

18:40.707 --> 18:42.743
HMM.

18:54.921 --> 18:57.257
♪♪♪♪

19:02.736 --> 19:03.937
HI.

19:03.937 --> 19:05.572
HELLO.

19:05.572 --> 19:06.773
HI.

19:06.773 --> 19:09.009
GIVE US A MINUTE,
WILL YOU?

19:09.009 --> 19:11.011
OH, I THOUGHT YOU WOULD'VE
CHANGED BY NOW.

19:11.011 --> 19:14.414
BELIEVE IT OR NOT,
I HAVEN'T BEEN HOME YET.

19:14.414 --> 19:18.819
I'M HEADED THERE AFTER THE
HEARING WITH THE BOTH OF YOU.

19:18.819 --> 19:20.320
DID YOU CALL TRIDMAN?

19:20.320 --> 19:21.688
YES.

19:21.688 --> 19:24.357
YES, AND?

19:24.357 --> 19:26.326
NOBODY WILL HELP US, JIM.

19:26.326 --> 19:27.528
WHAT?

19:27.528 --> 19:29.329
THEY DON'T WANT TO GET
THEIR HANDS DIRTY.

19:31.397 --> 19:32.866
NOBODY?

19:34.868 --> 19:37.137
NOPE.

19:37.137 --> 19:39.906
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

19:39.906 --> 19:43.844
YOU SHOULD SEE THE PRESS.
IT'S GONE NATIONAL.

19:43.844 --> 19:46.547
WELL, YOU CAN BLAME
MAGGIE DAY FOR THAT.

19:46.547 --> 19:47.614
SHE'S WORKING THIS ONE,
ISN'T SHE?

19:47.614 --> 19:48.414
MM‐HMM.

19:48.414 --> 19:51.017
YEAH.
IT WAS EASY TO DO.

19:51.017 --> 19:52.986
AND SHE'S EATING IT UP.

19:52.986 --> 19:54.855
I'M SURE SHE IS.

19:54.855 --> 19:56.923
I'M SURE SHE IS, TOO.

19:56.923 --> 19:58.324
HOW BAD IS IT?

19:58.324 --> 20:00.226
IT'S PRETTY BAD, JIM.

20:00.226 --> 20:02.636
WHAT'S DAVID SAYING,
KATHERYN?

20:02.636 --> 20:03.937
NOT MUCH.

20:03.937 --> 20:06.973
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?
IS HE TRYING TO GET ME OUT?

20:06.973 --> 20:09.409
UH...

20:09.409 --> 20:12.112
NO, VERONICA.

20:12.112 --> 20:13.547
WHY NOT?

20:13.547 --> 20:16.116
WHY NOT?

20:16.116 --> 20:19.052
VERONICA? REALLY?

20:19.052 --> 20:21.955
DID YOU NOT SEE YOUR PICTURE
IN THE PAPER?

20:21.955 --> 20:25.425
DID YOU NOT READ THE HEADLINES
IN THE PAPER?

20:25.425 --> 20:26.593
IF I WERE YOUR HUSBAND,

20:26.593 --> 20:28.695
I WOULD DO EVERYTHING
IN MY POWER TO MAKE SURE

20:28.695 --> 20:31.832
THAT YOUR ASS ROTS RIGHT HERE
IN THIS JAIL.

20:31.832 --> 20:33.299
JIM, JUST SHUT UP.

20:33.299 --> 20:35.401
NO, KATHERYN.

20:35.401 --> 20:37.638
LET HIM SPEAK.

20:37.638 --> 20:42.075
THANK YOU, VERONICA.
TELL HER THE TRUTH, KATHERYN.

20:42.075 --> 20:44.010
TELL HER THAT HER HUSBAND
IS HELL‐BENT

20:44.010 --> 20:46.847
ON LEAVING HER
RIGHT IN HERE.

20:51.752 --> 20:53.687
IS HE?

20:55.756 --> 20:57.524
HE'S WORKING ON
GETTING YOU OUT.

20:57.524 --> 20:59.526
NO.

20:59.526 --> 21:02.135
HE IS NOT WORKING ON
GETTING HER OUT.

21:04.337 --> 21:06.873
KATHERYN?

21:06.873 --> 21:08.441
TELL ME THE TRUTH.

21:08.441 --> 21:10.711
YES, KATHERYN,
YOU'RE HER DEAR FRIEND.

21:10.711 --> 21:13.680
TELL HER THE TRUTH.

21:13.680 --> 21:16.049
HE'S NOT.

21:16.049 --> 21:17.851
I'M SORRY.

21:17.851 --> 21:20.153
THE TRUTH.

21:22.255 --> 21:23.957
OKAY.

21:23.957 --> 21:27.728
GIVE ME THAT.

21:27.728 --> 21:32.265
[ SIGHS ]
YOU KEEP ENJOYING THIS, JIM.

21:32.265 --> 21:33.734
JUST KEEP IT UP.

21:33.734 --> 21:35.769
OH, I WILL, VERONICA,
I WILL.

21:35.769 --> 21:37.871
I'LL KEEP ENJOYING THIS.

21:37.871 --> 21:42.275
BUT I DO WANT YOU OUT OF HERE.
YOU HAVE NO IDEA.

21:42.275 --> 21:43.577
OH, I WILL GET OUT.

21:43.577 --> 21:44.945
NOT SOON ENOUGH.

21:44.945 --> 21:47.113
JUST A MINUTE.

21:47.113 --> 21:50.283
I HAVE CALLED MARTY HERE
TO HELP WITH THIS.

21:50.283 --> 21:52.886
LOOK,
I'VE REVIEWED YOUR CASE

21:52.886 --> 21:54.888
AND I'M SURE I CAN GET
BOTH OF YOU BAIL.

21:54.888 --> 21:57.223
I WILL BE REPRESENTING MYSELF,
THANK YOU.

21:57.223 --> 21:58.424
MRS. HARRINGTON...

21:58.424 --> 22:00.326
HOW MANY TIMES HAVE
I BEAT YOU, MARTY?

22:00.326 --> 22:01.367
THIS ISN'T A GOOD CASE.

22:01.367 --> 22:05.071
32, 33? I WILL BE
REPRESENTING MYSELF.

22:05.071 --> 22:06.640
YOU SHOULD BE REPRESENTED.

22:06.640 --> 22:08.308
I GOT ME.

22:09.510 --> 22:10.977
YOU TAKE CARE OF
THAT ASS OVER THERE.

22:13.479 --> 22:17.083
[ Voice breaking ]
MNH. WHEN DO WE GO?

22:18.519 --> 22:20.587
RIGHT NOW.

22:42.475 --> 22:48.314
♪♪♪♪

22:48.314 --> 22:49.215
HEY.

22:49.215 --> 22:50.316
WYATT.

22:50.316 --> 22:51.818
HEY.

22:51.818 --> 22:52.986
HEY, YOU RUSHED ME
DOWN HERE.

22:52.986 --> 22:53.954
ARE MY PARENTS OUT OR WHAT?

22:53.954 --> 22:55.656
YOUR MOTHER IS.

22:55.656 --> 22:56.356
WHAT?

22:56.356 --> 22:57.558
YES.

22:57.558 --> 22:58.625
WHERE IS SHE?

22:58.625 --> 23:00.894
WELL, SHE STOPPED BY
THE CAMPAIGN OFFICE,

23:00.894 --> 23:02.402
ACCORDING TO
ONE OF MY OFFICERS,

23:02.402 --> 23:05.171
AND SHE WAS HEADED HOME, BUT I
KNOW SHE'LL BE RIGHT BACK,

23:05.171 --> 23:08.909
BECAUSE YOUR FATHER IS HEADED IN
FOR A BAIL HEARING.

23:08.909 --> 23:10.210
WILL HE GET IT?

23:10.210 --> 23:11.411
NO. NOT A CHANCE.

23:11.411 --> 23:12.078
GOOD.

23:12.078 --> 23:13.980
[ SIGHS ]

23:13.980 --> 23:15.549
SO YOU OUT OF THERE?

23:15.549 --> 23:18.151
YEAH, I'M ALL PACKED.
EVERYTHING'S IN THE CAR.

23:18.151 --> 23:21.021
OKAY.

23:24.658 --> 23:27.327
HERE YOU GO.

23:27.327 --> 23:28.529
THIS IS IT?
YEAH.

23:28.529 --> 23:31.064
AND I CALLED THE BANK.

23:31.064 --> 23:32.999
WHAT,
YOU SPOKE TO MR. BOWMAN?

23:32.999 --> 23:34.500
I DID.

23:34.500 --> 23:35.602
HE'S NOT GOING TO
GIVE IT TO ME.

23:35.602 --> 23:36.570
HE DOESN'T HAVE A CHOICE.

23:36.570 --> 23:37.604
NO, HE'LL JUST CALL
MY MOTHER.

23:37.604 --> 23:40.006
HE WON'T.
IT'S SIGNED BY A JUDGE,

23:40.006 --> 23:42.042
AND IF HE DOESN'T TURN OVER
YOUR INHERITANCE,

23:42.042 --> 23:43.910
HE GOES TO JAIL.

23:43.910 --> 23:45.946
OKAY.

23:45.946 --> 23:49.616
AND HE HAS ALL OF THE PAPERWORK
FORCING HIM TO DO SO.

23:49.616 --> 23:51.518
AND YOU'RE SURE MY MOTHER
WON'T BE THERE?

23:51.518 --> 23:55.622
NO. THAT'S WHY I CALLED THE BAIL
HEARING FOR YOUR FATHER TODAY.

23:55.622 --> 23:58.058
WOW.

23:59.926 --> 24:00.901
SO JUST LIKE THAT?

24:00.901 --> 24:03.369
JUST LIKE THAT.

24:03.369 --> 24:06.172
WOW.

24:06.172 --> 24:07.541
THANK YOU.

24:07.541 --> 24:09.543
YOU'RE WELCOME.

24:09.543 --> 24:10.911
WYATT?

24:10.911 --> 24:12.145
YEAH.

24:12.145 --> 24:14.047
I'M COUNTING ON YOU.

24:14.047 --> 24:17.117
I'LL BE THERE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:17.117 --> 24:19.452
I'M FINE, OKAY?

24:19.452 --> 24:21.221
YEAH.

24:21.221 --> 24:23.456
I AM FINE, REALLY.

24:23.456 --> 24:25.692
LISTEN, I NEED YOU TO FIND
A PLACE TO LIVE,

24:25.692 --> 24:27.761
AND PLEASE DON'T TELL
YOUR PARENTS WHERE YOU ARE.

24:27.761 --> 24:28.962
RIGHT.

24:28.962 --> 24:30.063
OKAY.

24:30.063 --> 24:32.098
PLEASE GET OUT
OF THEIR HOUSE.

24:32.098 --> 24:34.434
OKAY, I WILL.
THANK YOU.

24:34.434 --> 24:35.135
OKAY.

24:35.135 --> 24:36.970
THANK YOU.

24:41.742 --> 24:45.679
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:45.679 --> 24:47.748
[ SIGHS ]

24:53.820 --> 24:57.423
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

24:57.423 --> 24:59.459
♪♪♪♪

25:02.603 --> 25:04.470
HELLO, HANNA.

25:04.470 --> 25:06.172
MR. HARRINGTON.

25:06.172 --> 25:09.175
WHAT HAPPENED IN HERE?

25:09.175 --> 25:11.678
WYATT.

25:11.678 --> 25:15.348
OH.

25:15.348 --> 25:16.950
ARE YOU GOING TO
CLEAN IT UP?

25:16.950 --> 25:21.121
NO.

25:21.121 --> 25:23.590
HEY, I...

25:23.590 --> 25:25.358
JUST CAME FROM
YOUR HOUSE.

25:27.861 --> 25:30.030
I'M VERY SORRY.

25:30.030 --> 25:33.033
I'LL BET YOU ARE.

25:33.033 --> 25:35.569
WHEN DID IT BURN DOWN?

25:35.569 --> 25:38.071
ONE DAY.

25:38.071 --> 25:41.141
HUH.

25:41.141 --> 25:44.578
I ‐‐ I KNEW IT WAS A LONG SHOT
FINDING YOU HERE.

25:44.578 --> 25:46.379
WHY IS THAT?

25:46.379 --> 25:48.782
I'M SURE YOU'RE AWARE
OF WHAT'S HAPPENED.

25:48.782 --> 25:50.416
WHAT IS THAT?

25:50.416 --> 25:53.119
WELL, IF YOU'RE NOT,
YOU WILL BE.

25:53.119 --> 25:55.088
WHAT?

25:55.088 --> 25:56.823
IT APPEARS THAT WYATT ‐‐

25:56.823 --> 25:58.391
HIT MY SON.

25:59.626 --> 26:01.568
YEAH.
AND THAT LITTLE GIRL.

26:01.568 --> 26:03.469
AND YOU ALL COVERED IT UP.

26:03.469 --> 26:05.606
THAT'S NOT ALTOGETHER TRUE.

26:05.606 --> 26:08.675
WHAT PART...NOT TRUE?

26:08.675 --> 26:12.312
HANNA, IT'S ‐‐ IT'S
AN OPEN INVESTIGATION.

26:12.312 --> 26:13.647
AND AS JIM'S COUNSEL,

26:13.647 --> 26:16.750
I'M NOT AT LIBERTY TO DISCUSS
THE DETAILS WITH YOU.

26:16.750 --> 26:20.687
OKAY.

26:20.687 --> 26:23.056
YOU UNDERSTAND THAT JIM
AND KATHERYN

26:23.056 --> 26:25.291
MAY NOT BE HOME
FOR QUITE A WHILE?

26:25.291 --> 26:28.862
I'M NOT LEAVING HERE
TILL I GET MY CHECK.

26:28.862 --> 26:30.430
I'LL WAIT.

26:30.430 --> 26:33.800
OKAY, BUT IT MAY BE
QUITE A WHILE.

26:33.800 --> 26:36.870
I NEED MY CHECK.

26:36.870 --> 26:38.972
OKAY.

26:38.972 --> 26:40.841
IF YOU KNEW THEY WEREN'T
GOING TO BE HERE,

26:40.841 --> 26:41.808
THEN WHY ARE YOU HERE?

26:41.808 --> 26:43.944
I WAS HOPING ON THE OFF CHANCE

26:43.944 --> 26:47.280
YOU'D BE HERE SO THAT
I COULD SPEAK WITH YOU.

26:47.280 --> 26:48.949
ABOUT?

26:48.949 --> 26:50.450
YOUR SON.

26:50.450 --> 26:52.853
WHAT ABOUT MY SON?

26:52.853 --> 26:56.690
THE NIGHT I CAME
TO YOUR HOUSE,

26:56.690 --> 26:59.492
AND YOUR SON HAD MY TRUCK,

26:59.492 --> 27:01.835
WAS MY WIFE THERE?

27:03.604 --> 27:05.038
WHAT'D YOU JUST SAY?

27:05.038 --> 27:09.042
IT'S AN OPEN INVESTIGATION,
AND AS JIM'S COUNSEL,

27:09.042 --> 27:12.145
YOU'RE NOT AT LIBERTY ‐‐
[ SCOFFS ]

27:12.145 --> 27:16.016
WELL, AS MY SON'S MOTHER,

27:16.016 --> 27:18.284
THERE'S AN OPEN
INVESTIGATION,

27:18.284 --> 27:21.522
I'M NOT AT LIBERTY TO
DISCUSS IT WITH YOU.

27:25.526 --> 27:29.362
HANNA, YOUR SON IS YOUNG,

27:29.362 --> 27:32.365
AND IT'S A VERY DANGEROUS GAME
HE'S INTO.

27:32.365 --> 27:36.603
DON'T YOU DARE THREATEN
MY SON.

27:36.603 --> 27:38.539
I'M NOT THREATENING
YOUR SON.

27:38.539 --> 27:41.107
YOU'D BETTER BE DAMN SURE
IT'S NOT A THREAT.

27:41.107 --> 27:44.344
'CAUSE I HAVE HAD IT WITH
YOU PEOPLE, AND ALL YOUR BULL...

27:46.112 --> 27:48.348
DON'T YOU DARE.

27:51.852 --> 27:55.355
WHAT I AM TELLING YOU
IS THAT MY WIFE

27:55.355 --> 27:57.423
CAN BE VERY CONNIVING
WHEN WHEN IT COMES TO

27:57.423 --> 27:58.424
GETTING WHAT SHE WANTS.

27:58.424 --> 28:00.260
THAT I KNOW.

28:00.260 --> 28:04.204
I JUST WANT TO MAKE SURE
THAT YOUR SON ISN'T CAUGHT UP

28:04.204 --> 28:06.607
IN A GAME THAT
SHE MAY BE PLAYING.

28:06.607 --> 28:08.875
VERONICA IS ONLY INTERESTED
IN SOMEONE

28:08.875 --> 28:12.078
IF THERE'S SOMETHING
SHE CAN GET OUT OF IT.

28:12.078 --> 28:15.181
INCLUDING YOU?

28:17.450 --> 28:21.454
YEAH. IT APPEARS SO.

28:21.454 --> 28:24.457
SO YOU'RE JUST TRYING
TO PROTECT MY SON?

28:24.457 --> 28:26.660
I AM.

28:26.660 --> 28:28.929
HOW?

28:28.929 --> 28:32.398
THE ONLY WAY
I CAN ANSWER THAT

28:32.398 --> 28:35.636
IF IS YOU TELL ME
EVERYTHING YOU KNOW.

28:37.070 --> 28:38.171
OKAY.

28:38.171 --> 28:41.241
LET ME TELL YOU WHAT I KNOW.

28:41.241 --> 28:43.409
PLEASE.

28:43.409 --> 28:47.581
I KNOW YOU THINK
I'M SOME IGNORANT‐ASS MAID

28:47.581 --> 28:50.150
WHO'S JUST GOING TO SIT HERE
AND LET YOU PLAY

28:50.150 --> 28:52.519
LIKE YOU'RE ON MY SON'S SIDE,

28:52.519 --> 28:54.387
AND LET ME TELL YOU
A BUNCH OF THINGS

28:54.387 --> 28:55.989
SO YOU CAN USE IT
AGAINST HIM.

28:55.989 --> 28:58.258
[ SIGHS ]

28:58.258 --> 29:01.935
I'M NOT GOING TO TELL YOU
A DAMN THING.

29:01.935 --> 29:03.804
♪♪♪♪

29:03.804 --> 29:06.406
I DON'T TRUST YOU.

29:06.406 --> 29:08.274
AND I DON'T LIKE YOU.

29:08.274 --> 29:11.344
YOU'RE A LIAR
AND THE TRUTH AIN'T IN YOU.

29:11.344 --> 29:15.081
NOW IF YOU DON'T MIND,

29:15.081 --> 29:19.820
I DON'T THINK I HAVE ANYTHING
ELSE TO SAY TO YOU, <i>DAVID.</i>

29:19.820 --> 29:24.958
NOW I'M GOING TO SIT HERE
AND WAIT FOR MY CHECK.

29:26.693 --> 29:29.229
IF YOU WANT TO KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT MY SON,

29:29.229 --> 29:30.964
YOU NEED TO GO ASK HIM.

29:30.964 --> 29:33.233
I ALREADY HAVE.

29:33.233 --> 29:35.501
AND WHAT DID HE SAY?

29:35.501 --> 29:38.304
ASK MY WIFE.

29:38.304 --> 29:40.006
IS THAT WHAT HE SAID?

29:40.006 --> 29:42.543
YES, HE DID.

29:42.543 --> 29:46.146
MNH. THAT'S WRONG.

29:46.146 --> 29:48.515
I RAISED MY BOY
BETTER THAN THAT.

29:48.515 --> 29:51.051
WHAT SHOULD HE HAVE SAID?

29:51.051 --> 29:56.389
HE SHOULD'VE SAID,
"ASK YOUR TRIFLING‐ASS WIFE."

29:56.389 --> 29:59.926
I'M GOING TO GET ON HIM
ABOUT THAT.

29:59.926 --> 30:02.869
HMM.

30:02.869 --> 30:05.438
"HMM"?

30:24.157 --> 30:26.560
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

30:26.560 --> 30:28.662
[ Ringing ]

30:28.662 --> 30:31.865
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]

30:37.971 --> 30:39.540
DAVID.

30:39.540 --> 30:40.874
OSCAR.

30:40.874 --> 30:42.142
WHAT'S UP?

30:42.142 --> 30:45.145
I NEED YOUR CONTACTS
AT THE PHONE COMPANY

30:45.145 --> 30:48.381
TO REROUTE ALL PHONE CALLS
FROM BENNY'S TOWING

30:48.381 --> 30:50.316
TO MEL GREEN'S TOWING.

30:50.316 --> 30:52.385
IMMEDIATELY.

30:52.385 --> 30:54.354
NEED TO STIR THINGS UP
OVER THERE.

30:54.354 --> 30:56.256
YEAH, SURE. I'M ON IT.

30:56.256 --> 30:58.124
THANK YOU.

31:06.072 --> 31:09.109
♪♪♪♪

31:09.109 --> 31:10.844
WHOO. TUCK.

31:10.844 --> 31:12.546
WYATT, WYATT, WYATT,
CHECK IT OUT.

31:12.546 --> 31:13.814
CHECK IT OUT, ALL RIGHT.
SO WHAT DO YOU THINK?

31:13.814 --> 31:15.115
YEAH. WHAT? WHAT?

31:15.115 --> 31:16.817
CHECK IT OUT, CHECK IT OUT.
SO WHAT DO YOU THINK?

31:16.817 --> 31:18.118
RIGHT THERE, RIGHT THERE.
LAST ONE, RIGHT HERE.

31:18.118 --> 31:18.785
I'LL TAKE IT.

31:18.785 --> 31:19.620
HUH? HUH? YEAH, BABY.

31:19.620 --> 31:20.787
[ Chuckling ] HEY.

31:20.787 --> 31:22.122
THERE'S NO BETTER PLACE
FOR A GUY LIKE YOU

31:22.122 --> 31:22.956
THAT LIKES TO PARTY.

31:22.956 --> 31:24.024
OF COURSE, MAN, YOU KNOW IT.

31:24.024 --> 31:25.826
TELL ME ‐‐ TELL ME ABOUT IT.
AM I RIGHT?

31:25.826 --> 31:28.028
AND THE CHICKS,
AND THE WIDE OPEN SPACE, MAN?

31:28.028 --> 31:29.563
THAT'S A COMPLETE
PANTY‐DROPPER.

31:29.563 --> 31:30.697
IT'S ON THE TOP FLOOR.

31:30.697 --> 31:31.998
THAT'S IT, RIGHT THERE.
I WANT THIS CONDO, HUH?

31:31.998 --> 31:32.899
OH, GREAT.

31:32.899 --> 31:34.100
MAKE IT HAPPEN.
LET'S GO.

31:34.100 --> 31:35.235
GREAT.

31:35.235 --> 31:36.269
YEAH?

31:36.269 --> 31:37.270
UH...

31:37.270 --> 31:39.239
LET'S GO, MAN.

31:39.239 --> 31:40.707
GREAT, MY MAN.
WHEN DO YOU WANT TO CLOSE?

31:40.707 --> 31:42.108
AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.
MAKE IT HAPPEN.

31:42.108 --> 31:44.410
[ LAUGHS ] WYATT.

31:44.410 --> 31:45.612
NAH, MAN, LET'S GO.
CALL THE OWNER,

31:45.612 --> 31:47.147
DO WHAT YOU GO TO DO,
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

31:47.147 --> 31:48.281
LE'S JUST DO IT. COME ON.
OKAY, OKAY.

31:48.281 --> 31:49.550
HOW ABOUT THIS?
HOW ABOUT THIS?

31:49.550 --> 31:51.417
I'LL GET THE OWNER
TO LEASE IT TO YOU SHORT‐TERM

31:51.417 --> 31:52.986
WITH ALL THE FURNITURE
UNTIL IT CLOSES?

31:52.986 --> 31:54.588
SOONER THE BETTER.

31:54.588 --> 31:55.589
I'LL CALL HIM NOW.
YEAH.

31:55.589 --> 31:56.389
LET'S DO IT.

31:56.389 --> 31:57.090
ALL RIGHT.

31:57.090 --> 31:58.525
HEY, WHILE YOU'RE AT IT...

31:59.560 --> 32:01.434
GET SOME CHICKS OVER HERE, TOO,
ALL RIGHT?

32:02.268 --> 32:03.336
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:03.336 --> 32:05.005
IS THAT ALL YOU WANT?

32:05.005 --> 32:06.640
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

32:06.640 --> 32:08.509
A LITTLE BLOW?

32:08.509 --> 32:10.611
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:10.611 --> 32:13.947
MY MAN.

32:13.947 --> 32:16.550
[ SIGHS ]

32:16.550 --> 32:17.417
[ SNIFFS ]

32:17.417 --> 32:18.685
RIGHT HERE, BABY.

32:18.685 --> 32:20.420
OH, YEAH. GIVE IT...

32:20.420 --> 32:21.688
GIVE IT ONE,
GIVE A SNIFF, HUH?

32:21.688 --> 32:22.956
THAT'S NICE, THAT'S NICE.
HUH?

32:22.956 --> 32:24.457
BUT YOU KNOW I HAD YOU
COVERED, RIGHT?

32:24.457 --> 32:25.592
YOU KNOW I HAD YOU
COVERED?

32:25.592 --> 32:29.429
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH, I GOT
MYSELF COVERED, BUDDY.

32:29.429 --> 32:31.264
WYATT, YOU KNOW THIS PLACE
IS $3 MILLION?

32:31.264 --> 32:34.300
YEAH. [ LAUGHS ]
YEAH. [ SIGHS ]

32:35.669 --> 32:36.837
LET'S GO, MAN,
MAKE THE CALL.

32:36.837 --> 32:37.904
LET'S GO.
DO WHAT YOU GOT TO DO.

32:37.904 --> 32:38.639
IT'S YOUR JOB.

32:38.639 --> 32:39.973
ARE YOU GOING TO SHARE?

32:39.973 --> 32:41.508
[ Chuckling ]
HELL, NO, MAN.

32:41.508 --> 32:43.476
YOU MAKE THE CALL,
I'LL SHARE ‐‐ MAYBE.

32:43.476 --> 32:44.978
WELL, I'LL MAKE THE CALL.
OKAY, THEN DO IT.

32:44.978 --> 32:46.613
MAKE THE CALL, AND COME
BACK HERE, AND WE'LL TALK.

32:53.720 --> 32:56.222
♪♪♪♪

32:56.222 --> 32:58.158
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

33:01.802 --> 33:02.803
[ GAVEL BANGS ]

33:02.803 --> 33:04.638
Judge: NEXT CASE.

33:04.638 --> 33:07.941
STATE OF GEORGIA vs.
JAMES WALTER CRYER.

33:09.776 --> 33:12.145
HOW DO YOU PLEAD?

33:12.145 --> 33:14.080
NOT GUILTY, YOUR HONOR.

33:14.080 --> 33:16.983
THE PEOPLE ARE ASKING
FOR NO BAIL.

33:16.983 --> 33:19.620
THAT IS RIDICULOUS,
YOUR HONOR.

33:19.620 --> 33:22.088
THIS MAN HAS BEEN NOTHING
BUT A MODEL CITIZEN.

33:22.088 --> 33:25.491
WHO COVERED UP A MURDER
TO PROTECT HIS SON.

33:25.491 --> 33:27.327
YOUR HONOR,
HE'S RUNNING FOR GOVERNOR,

33:27.327 --> 33:30.296
AND HE'S A VERY IMPORTANT PART
OF MRS. CRYER'S FAMILY HERE.

33:30.296 --> 33:32.766
WHICH IS HOW WE KNOW
HE HAS ACCESS TO PRIVATE JETS,

33:32.766 --> 33:33.499
AND HE CAN ‐‐

33:33.499 --> 33:35.602
HE WOULD NEVER DO THAT.

33:35.602 --> 33:37.303
OH, BUT HE WILL
COVER UP A MURDER?

33:37.303 --> 33:40.874
OKAY, OKAY, COUNSELORS.

33:40.874 --> 33:43.009
BAIL IS DENIED. NEXT CASE.

33:43.009 --> 33:44.945
WHAT?

33:44.945 --> 33:45.912
WHAT?!

33:45.912 --> 33:48.582
BAIL IS DENIED.
NEXT CASE.

33:48.582 --> 33:51.251
WHAT? SAMUEL?!

33:51.251 --> 33:52.452
YOU SMUG SON‐OF‐A‐BITCH.

33:52.452 --> 33:53.854
YOU'VE HAD IT OUT FOR ME
FOR YEARS, HAVEN'T YOU?

33:53.854 --> 33:55.088
MR. CRYER, PLEASE.

33:55.088 --> 33:56.923
DO YOU WANT TO BE HELD
IN CONTEMPT, JIM CRYER?

33:56.923 --> 33:58.825
WHY THE HELL NOT?
I'M ALREADY IN JAIL, AREN'T I?

33:58.825 --> 34:01.835
OKAY. 30 DAYS ON TOP
OF WHATEVER ELSE TIME

34:01.835 --> 34:03.036
IT TAKES YOU TO GET TO COURT.

34:03.036 --> 34:04.605
[ Chuckling ]
YOU SON‐OF‐A‐BITCH.

34:04.605 --> 34:06.372
WOULD YOU LIKE TO TRY FOR 60?

34:06.372 --> 34:09.242
JIM. JIM, ENOUGH.

34:15.215 --> 34:18.552
NEXT CASE.

34:18.552 --> 34:20.854
STATE OF GEORGIA vs.
VERONICA HARRINGTON.

34:34.167 --> 34:36.136
HOW DO YOU PLEAD?

34:36.136 --> 34:38.505
NOT GUILTY.

34:38.505 --> 34:43.209
YOUR HONOR, MRS. HARRINGTON
WILLFULLY WITHHELD INFORMATION

34:43.209 --> 34:46.146
IN A CRIME THAT RESULTED IN
THE DEATH OF A LITTLE GIRL

34:46.146 --> 34:47.180
IN A HIT‐AND‐RUN.

34:47.180 --> 34:50.416
THE STATE IS REQUESTING
NO BAIL.

34:50.416 --> 34:54.855
YOUR HONOR, I DID NOT DISCLOSE
THE LOCATION OF THE VEHICLE,

34:54.855 --> 34:57.490
BECAUSE I WAS GIVEN THAT
INFORMATION BY MY CLIENT,

34:57.490 --> 35:00.493
AND THAT INFORMATION WOULD
HAVE INCRIMINATED SAID CLIENT.

35:00.493 --> 35:04.004
NOW AS AN OFFICER
OF THE COURT,

35:04.004 --> 35:07.674
I WAS UNDER NO LEGAL OBLIGATION
TO TURN OVER THAT INFORMATION.

35:07.674 --> 35:11.578
THIS WAS HER SON.
SHE KNEW WHAT SHE WAS DOING.

35:11.578 --> 35:14.180
HE SAID SHE WAS NOT
REPRESENTING HIM.

35:14.180 --> 35:16.249
HOLD ON.
YOU WERE REPRESENTING YOUR SON?

35:16.249 --> 35:17.951
NO.

35:17.951 --> 35:19.352
YES, SIR, I WAS.

35:19.352 --> 35:22.088
AND I HAVE TOLD THIS D. A. THAT
ON SEVERAL OCCASIONS.

35:22.088 --> 35:25.559
D.A. SALLISON,
YOU ARE REACHING.

35:25.559 --> 35:29.095
JUDGE, HER SON WILL TESTIFY
THAT SHE DOESN'T REPRESENT HIM.

35:29.095 --> 35:32.332
WELL, THIS IS A BAIL HEARING,
NOT A COURT HEARING.

35:32.332 --> 35:34.134
YOU CAN ARGUE THAT AT TRIAL.

35:34.134 --> 35:36.369
MRS. HARRINGTON WILL BE RELEASED
ON HER OWN RECOGNIZANCE.

35:36.369 --> 35:37.037
THANK YOU, SIR.

35:37.037 --> 35:39.540
BUT, YOUR HONOR?!

35:39.540 --> 35:42.976
NEXT CASE.

35:42.976 --> 35:46.547
Bailiff: STATE OF GEORGIA
vs. JASON BARNES

35:46.547 --> 35:49.182
AND PHILLIP McSWAIN.

36:43.977 --> 36:44.911
HEY.

36:44.911 --> 36:46.580
Mitch: HEY.

36:46.580 --> 36:50.116
[ SIGHS ]
HOW'S IT BEEN LOOKING?

36:50.116 --> 36:52.986
WELL...YOU TELL ME.

36:52.986 --> 36:55.622
WHAT?

36:55.622 --> 36:58.258
LOOK AT THE BOARD.

36:59.993 --> 37:01.701
WHAT'S GOING ON?

37:01.701 --> 37:03.002
NOTICE ANYTHING?

37:03.002 --> 37:05.138
YEAH, THERE AIN'T
NO DAMN TOWS.

37:05.138 --> 37:07.373
PHONES AIN'T RINGING.

37:07.373 --> 37:08.775
[ Dial tone ]

37:08.775 --> 37:10.844
NO, THE PHONES ARE GOOD.
WHAT THE HELL?

37:10.844 --> 37:13.146
ALL I KNOW IS ONE MINUTE,

37:13.146 --> 37:14.681
THE PHONES ARE RINGING
OFF THE HOOK,

37:14.681 --> 37:15.849
AND THE NEXT, THEY'RE NOT.

37:15.849 --> 37:18.384
WHAT'S GOING ON, B.?

37:18.384 --> 37:19.520
I DON'T KNOW, MAN.

37:19.520 --> 37:22.055
YEAH, YEAH, YOU KNOW.

37:22.055 --> 37:23.056
NO, I DON'T.

37:23.056 --> 37:24.658
COME ON, BENNY.

37:24.658 --> 37:26.727
A SLOW DAY FOR US
IS ONE OR TWO TOWS.

37:26.727 --> 37:28.929
YOU'RE TELLING ME NOBODY'S
BREAKING DOWN OUT THERE TODAY?

37:28.929 --> 37:31.431
LOOK, MAN, I DON'T KNOW.
WE AIN'T BEEN AT IT THAT LONG.

37:31.431 --> 37:33.934
LOOK, EVER SINCE THIS
HARRINGTON DUDE ROLLED IN HERE,

37:33.934 --> 37:36.136
WE GOT NO TOWS
AND NO MONEY COMING IN.

37:36.136 --> 37:37.370
WAIT, WHAT?

37:37.370 --> 37:40.240
YOU ROLL OUT OF HERE WITH
A SHOVEL, LIME, AND PLASTIC.

37:40.240 --> 37:43.243
THEN THIS CAT WALKS IN HERE,
WHO'S RUNNING FOR GOVERNOR,

37:43.243 --> 37:44.745
HOUR LATER, WE GOT NO TOWS.

37:44.745 --> 37:45.846
LOOK, MAN, NONE OF THAT

37:45.846 --> 37:47.280
GOT NOTHING TO DO WITH
ANYTHING, ALL RIGHT?

37:47.280 --> 37:48.715
YEAH, ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
IF YOU SAY SO.

37:48.715 --> 37:49.449
YEAH, I KNOW SO.

37:49.449 --> 37:50.517
YEAH, ALL RIGHT.

37:54.020 --> 37:56.823
[ DIALING ]

37:56.823 --> 37:59.392
[ Ringing ]

38:01.267 --> 38:03.737
[ Dial tone ]

38:03.737 --> 38:05.371
YEAH, I TOLD YOU IT AIN'T
WORKING. I DONE ALL THAT.

38:05.371 --> 38:06.807
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

38:06.807 --> 38:10.711
[ Dial tone ]

38:10.711 --> 38:12.045
[ Ringing ]

38:12.045 --> 38:13.914
I DID THE SAME THING.

38:13.914 --> 38:17.250
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]

38:19.620 --> 38:21.655
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

38:24.390 --> 38:25.892
WHAT THE HELL, BENNY?

38:33.233 --> 38:35.201
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]

38:35.201 --> 38:38.138
[ MUMBLES ]

38:38.138 --> 38:39.573
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

38:39.573 --> 38:41.742
HI, CANDACE.

38:41.742 --> 38:44.177
HOW ARE YOU?

38:44.177 --> 38:47.447
I'M...GREAT.

38:47.447 --> 38:50.150
I'D LOVE TO, BUT I HAVE TO ‐‐

38:50.150 --> 38:54.921
I HAVE TO PUT OUT A SMALL FIRE
AT THE OFFICE.

38:54.921 --> 38:57.958
OKAY, COOL. BYE.

38:57.958 --> 38:59.793
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

38:59.793 --> 39:01.968
Maggie: [ CRYING ]

39:10.176 --> 39:12.613
DRY YOUR EYES.

39:12.613 --> 39:15.782
[ SNIFFLES ]

39:17.350 --> 39:20.554
YOU WANT TO SAY,
"I TOLD YOU SO"?

39:20.554 --> 39:23.456
WHAT HAPPENED?

39:23.456 --> 39:26.593
DAVID'S PISSED AT ME.

39:28.061 --> 39:32.198
I SHOULDN'T HAVE DONE THIS.
I SHOULDN'T HAVE DONE THIS.

39:32.198 --> 39:35.435
NO, YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE.

39:35.435 --> 39:37.403
DAVID, DAVID,
I AM SO SORRY.

39:37.403 --> 39:38.572
MR. HARRINGTON,
SHE WAS JUST ‐‐

39:38.572 --> 39:39.706
I HAVE NOTHING
TO SAY TO YOU.

39:39.706 --> 39:41.742
I WAS JUST TRYING TO...

39:43.910 --> 39:45.612
BENJAMIN YOUNG.

39:50.584 --> 39:52.886
DECIDED TO COME SEE ME
AFTER ALL?

39:52.886 --> 39:55.388
YOU DECIDED TO HAVE
SOMETHING DONE TO MY PHONES.

39:55.388 --> 39:57.858
IN MY OFFICE.

39:59.526 --> 40:01.968
WHAT'S GOING ON?

40:01.968 --> 40:04.437
[ SNIFFLES ]

40:14.781 --> 40:17.183
YOU'RE HAVING AN AFFAIR
WITH MY WIFE.

40:17.183 --> 40:18.284
WHAT'D YOU DO TO
MY PHONES?

40:18.284 --> 40:20.053
I NEED TO KNOW
WHAT'S BEEN GOING ON

40:20.053 --> 40:23.557
BETWEEN YOU AND MY WIFE,
AND I NEED TO KNOW NOW.

40:23.557 --> 40:25.425
LOOK, MAN,
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU DID,

40:25.425 --> 40:27.994
BUT I WANT MY PHONES BACK
ON LINE, I WANT 'EM ON NOW.

40:27.994 --> 40:30.230
YOUNG MAN, YOU ARE WAY
OUT OF YOUR DEPTH.

40:30.230 --> 40:31.932
I DON'T WANT YOUR WIFE,
ALL RIGHT?!

40:31.932 --> 40:32.966
IT HAPPENED ONE TIME.

40:32.966 --> 40:34.400
WELL, A FEW TIMES.
WHATEVER.

40:34.400 --> 40:35.301
SHE CAME AFTER ME.

40:35.301 --> 40:35.969
ALL RIGHT?

40:35.969 --> 40:37.203
YOU JUST LEAVE ME ALONE

40:37.203 --> 40:39.305
AND WE'RE GOING TO KEEP
ALL THIS COOL. YOU UNDERSTAND?

40:39.305 --> 40:40.641
'CAUSE I KNOW YOU PLAYING
SOME TYPE OF GAMES

40:40.641 --> 40:41.842
WITH MY PHONES, MAN.

40:41.842 --> 40:44.845
I GOT BILLS TO PAY
AND I AIN'T INTO THESE GAMES.

40:44.845 --> 40:46.513
AND I KNOW HOW YOU ROLL.

40:46.513 --> 40:49.816
YEAH, YOU AND THESE, UH...
THESE CRYERS. MY SISTER TOLD ME.

40:49.816 --> 40:51.785
THEN YOU SHOULD KNOW
TO ANSWER MY QUESTIONS

40:51.785 --> 40:53.053
ABOUT YOU AND MY WIFE.

40:53.053 --> 40:54.588
NO, YOU SHOULD PROBABLY ASK
YOUR LITTLE WIFE ABOUT THAT.

40:54.588 --> 40:55.856
TELL ME EVERYTHING NOW

40:55.856 --> 40:58.158
OR YOUR PHONES WILL BE
THE LEAST OF ‐‐

40:58.158 --> 40:59.993
HEY, HEY,
YOU DIDN'T THREATEN ME!

40:59.993 --> 41:01.034
YOU HEAR ME?!

41:01.034 --> 41:02.936
I'LL KNOCK YOUR OLD ASS OUT
RIGHT NOW.

41:02.936 --> 41:04.605
YOU ARROGANT SON‐OF‐A‐BITCH,
I'LL ‐‐

41:04.605 --> 41:05.772
MR. HARRINGTON?

41:05.772 --> 41:07.073
WHAT?!

41:07.073 --> 41:08.108
YOUR WIFE BAILED OUT.

41:08.108 --> 41:09.943
THEY RELEASED HER
FROM JAIL?

41:09.943 --> 41:11.044
YES, SHE'S HEADED HOME.

41:11.044 --> 41:13.880
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY!

41:18.619 --> 41:20.186
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

41:26.059 --> 41:27.894
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

41:28.128 --> 41:30.296
<i>NEXT ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

41:30.296 --> 41:32.799
NEED TO FIND MY BROTHER.
THE PHONE IS HERE.

41:32.799 --> 41:35.135
VERONICA HARRINGTON,
YOU ARE FREE TO GO.

41:35.135 --> 41:36.136
OF COURSE, I AM.

41:36.136 --> 41:37.437
YOU KNOW WHAT SHE SAID?
QUITA?

41:37.437 --> 41:38.905
SHE SAID SHE WAS LOOKING
FOR HER BROTHER.

41:38.905 --> 41:40.707
HOW EXHAUSTED ARE YOU?
PRETTY EXHAUSTED.

41:40.707 --> 41:42.743
TOO EXHAUSTED TO MEET
A NICE, HOT MAN?

41:42.743 --> 41:46.079
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

41:46.079 --> 41:49.449
VERONICA, I NEED YOUR HELP.
I'M QUINCY'S SISTER.

41:49.449 --> 41:50.283
[ Ringing ]

41:50.283 --> 41:51.585
HELLO?

41:51.585 --> 41:52.853
DON'T LET VERONICA LEAVE.

41:52.853 --> 41:53.820
She's already out.

41:53.820 --> 41:54.988
LOOKS LIKE YOU ENJOYED IT.

41:54.988 --> 41:56.156
IF YOU EVER DO THAT AGAIN,

41:56.156 --> 41:58.158
I'LL BLOW YOUR BRAINS
ALL OVER THIS WALL.
